The paper deals with the fully dynamic single-source reachability problem in graphs, which involves maintaining the set of vertices that are reachable from a given vertex subject to edge deletions and insertions. This problem is related to data structures (cs.DS), graph algorithms (cs.GR), and network science (cs.SI). The paper also involves experimental evaluation of algorithms, which could fall under data mining (cs.DM) or networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
